column5: Gonna get a new aluminum prop this weekend from Kawartha Prop in Buckhorn.  Been looking on line.  Can get several brands for about $150  (13 in x 19p)  Would rather buy local.  perhaps they would exchange in case got the wrong one.  Not sure what brands they carry.  Likely don't carry junk.  Any brands to be avoided?
I was told by a Prop repair guy, if you want a new prop go with Solas.
Stop in at the Prop Drop on hwy #35 just south of Lindsay as well. He's been really good to me over the years, and has an awesome selection of props.  S.
